                        "definition": "Medical advice provided to patients in outpatient health care per capita.",
                      
                        "unit": "pieces",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "Medical advice is a health service provided by a physician, dentist or psychologist. Outpatient health services are the provision of primary or specialist health care and services in the field of medical rehabilitation, provided in conditions that do not require their provision in a stationary and 24-hour mode in an appropriately equipped, permanent room. The provision of these services may take place on the premises of the enterprise, including in a vehicle intended for the provision of these services, or at the patient's place of stay.",
                      
